# Ambx â€” Ruby USB driver and applications for Philips amBX devices

By Etienne van Delden de la Haije, Martijn de Boer, and Gert-Jan de Boer. See AUTHORS for details.

A cross-platform Ruby toolkit for controlling Philips amBX USB devices from macOS and Linux.

Licensed under the BSD license. See LICENSE for details.

## Applications

| App | Location | Description |
|-----|----------|-------------|
| `menubar` | `applications/menubar/` | macOS status-bar app with color and fan presets |
| `ambilight` | `applications/ambilight/` | Screen-capture ambient light loop |
| `boblight` | `applications/boblight/` | stdin bridge for the Boblight/XBMC protocol |
| `setcolor` | `applications/setcolor/setcolor.rb` | One-shot CLI to set all lights |
| `setfan` | `applications/setcolor/setfan.rb` | One-shot CLI to set both fans |

## Library

`libambx/` is the canonical driver tree. Applications consume an `Ambx::Session`; they do not talk to USB handles or raw packet bytes directly.

```ruby
require "libambx"

session = Ambx::Session.open

session.lights.set(:left, Ambx::Color.rgb(255, 0, 0))
session.lights.set_all(Ambx::Color.rgb(255, 244, 229), green_boost: 1.0)
session.fans.set_all(128)

session.brightness.adjust(-1)

listener = session.input_listener
listener.on(:brightness) { |event| session.brightness.adjust(event.delta) }

session.close
```

### Public API

| Type | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `Ambx::Session` | Opens the device transport and exposes the application-facing banks |
| `Ambx::Color` | RGB value object with clamping and scaling helpers |
| `Ambx::Brightness` | Brightness level state and replay coordination |
| `Ambx::LightBank` | Tracks and writes the five light zones |
| `Ambx::FanBank` | Writes left and right fan speeds |
| `Ambx::Packet` | Builds exact six-byte USB packets |
| `Ambx::Protocol` | USB IDs, endpoints, opcodes, and device ID parsing |
| `Ambx::Input::Listener` | Background input polling and event dispatch |
| `Ambx::Input::Event` | Typed input event object |
| `Ambx::Input::RotaryDecoder` | Packet-to-event decoder |

### Errors

`Ambx::Session.open` raises typed driver errors instead of returning booleans:

- `Ambx::Error::NoDeviceFound`
- `Ambx::Error::OpenFailed`
- `Ambx::Error::ClaimFailed`
- `Ambx::Error::Disconnected`
- `Ambx::Error::InputUnavailable`

### Protocol constants

Compatibility constants remain available for packet tests and low-level debugging:

- `Ambx::Lights`
- `Ambx::Fans`
- `Ambx::Rumbler`

Additional compatible device IDs can be supplied with `AMBX_USB_DEVICE_IDS`:

```bash
AMBX_USB_DEVICE_IDS=1234:abcd,0x5678:0x9abc bundle exec ruby your_app.rb
```

## Dependencies

```text
Ruby  >= 3.0        (developed and tested on Ruby 4.0)
libusb              system library â€” brew install libusb
libusb gem          runtime dependency of libambx
ruby-vips           required by repository apps only
```

Full instructions: `INSTALL`

## CLI tools

```bash
bundle exec ruby applications/setcolor/setcolor.rb 255 0 0
bundle exec ruby applications/setcolor/setfan.rb 128
```

## Testing

Unit tests run without a physical device. USB calls are stubbed.

```bash
bundle exec rake test
```

The suite uses Minitest with `describe` and `it` blocks.

